cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.AR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance of LoRa technology in indoor environments, which is related to networking and communication.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper investigates the large-scale fading characteristic and temporal fading characteristic of LoRa technology, which are related to information theory.
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is a possible category as the paper studies the coverage and energy consumption of LoRa technology, which can be relevant to multi-agent systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the importance of parameter selection and enabling LoRa adaptive data rate feature in energy-limited applications, which can be related to systems and control.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve hardware-related aspects of LoRa technology.
